Pre-Game Insights: Australia enter the T20 World Cup 2024 with the goal of making history as the first country to hold the title in all three formats of cricket.
Defending champions England come into the match after having their first game of the tournament against Scotland washed out.
Jos Buttler will need to refind their attacking Bazball style that worked so well for them if they fancy a chance of successfully defending their title.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch at the Kensington Oval provides equal opportunities for batters and bowlers. The average first innings score here is 137.
The maximum temperature is expected to be around 27°C but there is a looming rain threat with a 40 percent chance of showers.
